<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be a know-all • know it all</xh5><p> <i>be a know-all—</i>said of smb. who thinks he knows everything and annoys people by showing how clever he is: I don’t see the point in arguing with someone who plays such a <u>knowall</u>.</p><p><i>know it all—</i>1. be extremely knowledgeable; be fully informed: Did he choose the Pharisees and the Sadducees—the scribes and men who did nothing all day but study the scripture—men who <u>knew it all</u>? 2. is often used with the implication of overconfidence: The older I get, the more I realize that my dad really did know what he was talking about (but I was a young punk who “<u>knew it all</u>”...).</p> </entry>
